The metric used to measure reasoning depth is called ENL-50, which is defined as the maximum number of needles (N) for which the model's exact-match accuracy (PN) remains at least 50%. This is based on the following equation:

ENLτ= max{N∈N|PN≥τ}

where τ is a threshold (set to 50% in this case).
